HEADWORD: gin mill
<hw>gin mill</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A
commercial establishment where alcoholic drinks are served over a
counter; a barroom; -- a disparaging term suggesting a cheap or
disreputable bar.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> barroom, bar-room, bar, saloon, taproom.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ginnee</ent>⟦br⟧
